scopecontent.p:
Correspondents discuss camp life; winter quarters; marches;
         deserters with forged papers and the shooting of deserters;
         illnesses and deaths in battles; prisoners of war,
         particularly the care and transportation of wounded and ill
         Confederates; picket duty and friendly exchanges across the
         lines; hostile behavior against African American troops;
         England's attitude; a comparison of McClellan vs Hooker; and
         opinion of Halleck.
